The paper proposes a method for reducing computation in convolutional neural networks (CNNs) by sparsely sampling feature maps and interpolating them. This is a common problem in computer vision, which falls under the category of cs.CV. The paper also introduces a reparameterization trick based on the Gumbel-Softmax distribution, which is a technique used in machine learning and optimization, falling under the categories of cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.NE. Finally, the paper discusses the use of backpropagation, which is a fundamental technique in deep learning and neural networks, falling under the category of cs.CL.
